UIComponent defines the basic behaviour of a UIComponent without data. These include the default states of a component, the way it should change between states and a helper function to create a new skin. To create a component, extend UIComponent and override the following methods: - createStates - createBehaviours - createChildren - createSkin - removeStates - removeSkin - disposeChildren Non of these methods need to call their super methods because they are empty.
